                <div class="post_details">
                    <p class="this_article"><strong>In this article:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><a href="#">What Is LED Light Therapy?</a></li>
                        <li><a href="#">How LED light therapy works</a></li>
                        <li><a href="#">Benefits of LED Light Therapy</a></li>
                        <li><a href="#">How to Prepare</a></li>
                        <li><a href="#">LED Light Therapy vs. Microneedling</a></li>
                        <li><a href="#">At-Home vs. In Clinic</a></li>
                        <li><a href="#">Are At-Home LED devices safe?</a></li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="growing_post pt-40">
                    <p>Growing in popularity over the last few years, LED light therapy promises to fight
                        acne and signs of aging with the use of light technology. Pair this with the funky
                        device that will make you look like you’re futuristic in the year 2165, and you have
                        the beauty treatment every beauty lover is desperate to try.</p>
                    <p>Here you are probably wondering how exactly can a device that emits bright LED lights
                        aid to have a clearer and brighter complexion? Better yet, transform your skin?</p>
                    <p>If you are frustrated by things like wrinkling, sagging skin, acne and inflammation.
                        LED light therapy is a must try for you! The beauty devices have been used by our
                        favourite celebrities like Kourtney Kardashian and Jessica Alba. You’d have to agree
                        when we say that innovative beauty products are so much more fun. We thought we’d
                        give you the rundown on everything you need to know about LED light therapy. What it
                        is, how it works, and any other must-know information about this life changing skin
                        treatment.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="what_led pt-40">
                    <p class="fs-24"><strong>What is LED light therapy?</strong></p>
                    <p>LED means light-emitting diode. LED light therapy is a noninvasive approach that
                        works by emitting infrared lights in different wavelengths/spectrums, which have
                        distinct skincare benefits. Red light is the most frequently used light to promote
                        circulation. Blue light kills bacteria.</p>
                    <p>During an LED light therapy at-home treatment, the device sends light waves deep into
                        the skin to trigger natural intracellular reactions. Depending on which light is
                        being used, the skin will respond differently. Using the red light, your skin
                        responds by building, strengthening and maximizing cellular structure. Red light is
                        additionally believed to target oil glands and reduce cytokines, which are
                        responsible for inflammation and play a role in chronic acne. If you opt to use the
                        blue light, specific wavelengths stimulate production of oxygen radicals that kill
                        P.acnes bacteria.</p>
                    <p>And, all of this is done without damaging the skin.</p>
                </div>
                <figure class="inline-promo-card">
                    <picture>
                        <source media="(min-width:768px)" srcset="sections/isolated/blogs/images/discover_best_seller.webp">
                        <img src="sections/isolated/blogs/images/discover_best_seller_mob.webp" alt="">
                    </picture>
