                <div class="led_vs_microneedling">
                    <p class="fs-24"><strong>LED Light Therapy vs. Microneedling</strong></p>
                    <p>Micro-needling is another popular facial treatment to rejuvenate the skin. It can
                        improve signs of ageing, acne, scarring and pigmentation.</p>
                    <p>The needles create microscopic wounds on the top layer of the skin and ignite the
                        body’s natural defence is to repair the wounds, causing collagen regeneration to
                        create new tissue and the result is a fresher, younger looking appearance.</p>
                    <p>The benefits are the same as LED light therapy, but a little more invasive.</p>
                    <p>Often facial treatment in-clinics include the combination of LED light and
                        microneedling in one visit to effectively treat multiple skin concerns. The treated
                        skin is exposed to LED light therapy after micro-needling or microdermabrasion to
                        maximise results. LED light is clinically proven to stimulate cellular activity,
                        therefore encouraging collagen production. LED light therapy will further reduce
                        fine lines and wrinkles , improve scarring, clear blemishes, improve skin tone, and
                        repair sun damage. Some experts might label this combination as the “perfect
                        pair”.</p>
                </div>
                <figure class="inline-promo-card">
                    <picture>
                        <source media="(min-width:768px)" srcset="sections/isolated/blogs/images/skin_journey.webp">
