                <div class="led_safe_at_home pt-30 pt-md-60">
                    <p class="fs-24"><strong>Are At-Home LED devices safe?</strong></p>
                    <p>The testing for at-home devices is actually more rigorous than professional ones
                        because the device is being cleared to use without the presence of a professional –
                        there's a higher-level burden of proof to show efficacy and safety because a
                        consumer is in charge of their own treatment.</p>
                    <p>An at-home device like the Q-Rejuvalight Pro Facewear is a seriously effective option
                        to invest in.</p>
                    <p>Q-Rejuvalight Pro Facewear offers a three-minute treatment with a combination of 100
                        red LED lights and 62 blue LED lights; is non-thermal and does not use UV light.
                        It’s equipped with an automatic shut off feature, heat regulators and timer.</p>
                    <p>Unlike any other device on the market, the Q-Rejuvalight Pro Facewear comes with a
                        compatible iOS/ Android app which allows you to totally customize every treatment
                        according to your skin concerns. Whether it be programming red lights on your
                        forehead and eye area whilst having blue lights on your chin and nose.</p>
                    <p>With a device like this, you are able to perform daily LED light therapy treatments,
                        totally customized to your own skin, and get maximum benefits. It’s a certain way to
                        transform your own skin without the trips to the salons and “clinical” price
                        tags. and get long term benefits.</p>
                </div>
